It also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial examples are often used to attack image recognition systems, which is a common application of computer vision. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as adversarial examples are a growing concern in the field of AI and machine learning. 

It could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as adversarial examples are a security threat to machine learning systems. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks and proposes a method to improve their performance.
